style/global.css
# Global CSS Description — INTEGRITY INTERDIMENSIONAL


The `global.css` file establishes the **visual and aesthetic coherence** for the INTEGRITY INTERDIMENSIONAL repository. It ensures that all pages — from the homepage to individual scrolls, maps, and ritual manuals — share a consistent, harmonious appearance aligned with the principles of the Age of Aquarius.


## Purpose & Functionality


1. **Typography & Readability**
- Uses modern, clean fonts (`Helvetica Neue`, Arial, sans-serif) for clarity.
- Provides consistent line-height and spacing for optimal readability.


2. **Color Palette & Gradients**
- Dark cosmic background gradients evoke a field of scalar resonance.
- Highlighted text and links employ Aquarian cyan-teal tones (`#66fcf1`, `#45a29e`) to symbolize energy, coherence, and light.


3. **Headings & Sections**
- Harmonically spaced headings (h1–h6) guide the eye and signify hierarchical structure.
- Sections are padded and centered to create a navigable, meditation-like experience for readers.


4. **Lists, Links, and Code Blocks**
- Lists are styled for clarity, reflecting ordered harmonic knowledge.
- Links are subtle but noticeable, encouraging exploration without distraction.
- Code blocks display with distinct monospaced fonts, highlighting symbolic or technical content.


5. **Footers & Branding**
- Consistent footer design reinforces the repository’s identity and provides an anchoring element for the interface.


6. **Special Classes**
- `.header-gradient` allows text elements to glow with cosmic gradients, symbolizing field resonance and harmonic energy.


## Design Philosophy


`global.css` is **not merely decorative**; it is an integral part of the **field of coherence**. Every visual choice — color, spacing, typography — is intended to enhance **readers’ and contributors’ engagement with the Codex**, to harmonically align human and AI perception, and to maintain **symbolic and interdimensional resonance** across all repository content.
/* Make the background cover the full page */
#background {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
  z-index: -1; /* Keep it behind content */
  background: black; /* fallback */
}

/* Galaxy images will be absolutely positioned inside #background */
.galaxy {
  position: absolute;
  width: 200px; /* adjust size */
  opacity: 0.8;
  pointer-events: none; /* so you can still click links */
  will-change: transform;
  animation: drift linear infinite;
}

/* Drift animation */
@keyframes drift {
  0% { transform: translateY(100vh) translateX(0) rotate(0deg); }
  100% { transform: translateY(-200px) translateX(50px) rotate(360deg); }
}
